Brad Merhtens is my favorite teacher I've had my entire life.  He explaings the material very well and if you're not sure about something he is awesome at explaining things.  He also acts a little like Ben Stiller and is always good for a laugh.  Take his classes.

Haha.. He's really funny and is a great speaker who lectures clearly and knows what he's talking about. Make sure to take notes, and re-read the powerpoint slides before a test, and you should be fine.
Tests are tough, but one of the best professors I've ever had! He really knows what he's talking about and take advantage of his office hours!

the class isn't terribly difficult, but it requires a lot of cramming for exams.. extremely thorough lecturer, well versed in biology, and there's a web forum for questions you have. the tests are comprehensive and tricky, but not unfair. teaching-wise, he's great
Great professor! Gives tough exams, watch for trick questions! Thoroughly explained all lecture material... just make sure you go to lecture! All exam material is from lecture!
One of the best biology teachers I have had. He lectures really well, and he is extremely helpful and organized. Tests are hard but they represent class material.

Excellent teacher with excellent classroom graphics and notes.  The notebook was a BIG help.  Though he doesn't have his doctorate, his conceptual understanding of the material was great.  Bellini has mites.
He has a good sense of humor and really knows what he's talking about. He talks fast though and is a big help if you've already had AP Bio
liked the class! although he speaks kinda fast, sometimes hard to follow

explains very clear and is very nice.  knows his stuff and has a good sense of humor.  the practice exams helped a lot, and many times some of the same questions on the practice exam appeared on the actual test.  i like how he reiterates facts because it helps you remember the information.

I hated his anal retentiveness and the fact that his exams were so detailed when he clearly stated they wouldn't be...and I didn't understand why he taught from the MCB 252 book when we were not required to buy it and clearly had our own 150 dollar text book for the course
I think he is an amazing professor because he is easy to understand, yet he keeps the class moving at a very quick pace so it keeps it challenging.
SOO MEAN!
He is a good teacher and wants you to understand, but you have to write papers in discussion about boring subjects and he has a lot of trick questions on his test so read them carefully.
best professor i have had yet. you don't need a doctorate to teach this class material.

Very good, clear lecturer. He really knows his stuff and tries hard to help his students.  Lots of office hours, review sessions, very personable and accesably. As long as you can memorize the notes, the exams are pretty easy.
